            <p><addressee>Revnd Mr Leeser</addressee>â€”<date>March 24th-49</date></p>
            <p><persName role="author">Mrs Eckard</persName>
                <placeName>No 68 So 8th St.</placeName><lb/> takes the liberty of requesting<lb/>
                tickets of admission, if tickets are<lb/> required, to the Consecration, of the<lb/>
                new Synagogue in <placeName>Crown St.</placeName>
                <persName role="author">Mrs<lb/> Eckard</persName> has several friends
                strangers<lb/> in the City, who no doubt would<lb/> be happy to witness the
                solemn<lb/> and interesting scene. We all<lb/> love your people my dear Sir.
                The<lb/> time is not far distant when we, as<lb/> dear <persName>Miss
                    Aguillar</persName> now does, shall<lb/> see<lb/> "Eye to Eye." May I beg you
                sir, in<lb/> case you <sic>authorise</sic> our admission<lb/> to say at what hour we
                had best<lb/> be there. With Great respect</p>
            <p><persName role="author">Susan R E</persName>___</p>
